shared_text:
Brad DeBeer
August 31 at 10:59 PM ¬∑

Hello Dolphin Nation! I have a fantastic opportunity for you to own a piece of Deubrook history! This past Saturday we held our first ever Don Ray Invitational Cross Country Meet. We made the decision a year ago to change the name of our Invitational to honor Mr. Ray for all he has done for Dolphin Nation and the Cross Country programs. That being said, the Cross country team is selling these shirts. We give the top 20 place winners in each varsity division one of these shirts. We had so many positive comments and questions about the shirts that we have decided to place another order for all that want to buy one or more shirts. Cost is just $10/shirt or $11 for 2XL or larger. If you would like to place an order for any of the colors please text me at 605-695-0020, email me at brad.debeer@k12.sd.us or catch me at a Dolphin event this week. Please let me know size and color! Orders and payment due by Sunday, September 6. Please contact me with questions. Thank you. #GOPHINS #DOLPHINNATION
~~Coach DeBeer

DVC All-Conference - Baylee Holmlund - 2nd Team
Claire Olsen - Honorable Mention
Most Improved - Emma "Essie" Sheffield
Newcomer Award - Ellie Koenig
Dolphin Spirit - Ashley Landmark
Co-MVP - Baylee Holmlund & Claire Olsen

~~Coach DeBeer

post_text: It's easy to smile after wins...everyone loves winning...but this team continues to humble me and impress me with their character. Tonght we fell in the DVC Championship game at the hands of a deserving hot shooting Estelline/Hendricks team. It's our first defeat of the season and as a coach losing always hurts, but this team in the locker room after the loss was as focused on what we want to accomplish this season as they were the first day of practice. Sports reveals character and I'm more than excited to see this team continue to improve and reveal the unbelievably great character they have. Dolphin Nation, THANK YOU for your support in THE K tonight! Love this team. #BLESSED #SISTERHOOD #INVEST #DOLPHINNATION #GOPHINS
